---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import MilesExplorer from '../components/MilesExplorer.svelte';
import { loadLifetimeMiles } from '../lib/data';

const data = await loadLifetimeMiles();
---

<Layout>
  <article>
    <section>
      <h1>In Memorium</h1>
      <div class="intro-row">
        <p>
          Honey the Syrian long-haired hamster (full name: Honey the Destroyer of Worlds, Killer of
          Men, Five-time Olympic Gold Medalist) passed away on January 18th, 2022. An avid runner,
          Honey clocked more than <strong>1,886 miles</strong> in her hamster wheel in less than two years.
          When asked if her diet was the key to her fitness prowess, she was known to remark, "...", with
          her cheeks full of secrets. (<a href="/history">How did we know?</a>)
        </p>
        <video
          src="/wheel-run.mp4"
          autoplay
          loop
          muted
          playsinline
          class="selfie intro-video tilt-right-2"
          aria-label="Honey running in her wheel"></video>
      </div>

      <MilesExplorer {data} client:load />

      <img
        src="/honey-pullup.jpg"
        alt="Honey the Hamster doing a pull-up on her cage bars"
        height="175"
        class="selfie right tilt-right-5"
      />
      <img
        src="/honey-shot-first.jpg"
        alt="Honey the Hamster looking mischievous"
        height="175"
        class="selfie right tilt-left-2"
      />
      <p>
        Honey loved travel as much as she loved working out. Her favorite exotic destinations
        included Narnia Under the Couch, the Lower Bookcase Shelf Next to the Legos, and Behind the
        Master Bath Toilet. Never one to miss an opportunity to scratch her back at a baseboard
        corner, Honey took time to sniff the world while out and about. Her 20 minute forays left
        her fulfilled and ready to return home at the call of her name to her waiting wheel, snack
        sticks, water bottle, and soft bedding.
      </p>

      <p>
        Honey now rests in a mossy plot in The Great Backyard. She is survived by her three
        caretakers. Donations can be made to the <a href="https://www.aspca.org/">ASPCA</a> in lieu of
        flowers.
      </p>

      <div class="final-media">
        <img
          src="/honey-lap.jpg"
          alt="Honey the Hamster sitting in a lap"
          height="200"
          class="selfie tilt-right-2"
        />
        <img
          src="/honey-cheeks.jpg"
          alt="Honey the Hamster with her cheeks full"
          height="200"
          class="selfie tilt-left-2"
        />
      </div>
    </section>

    <hr />

    <section>
      <p class="footer">
        For more photos of the life and times of Honey, visit <a
          href="https://www.instagram.com/honey_thebesthamster/">honey_thebesthamster</a
        > on Instagram.
      </p>
      <p class="footer">
        Curious how the wheel was tracked? <a href="/history">See how it worked.</a>
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .selfie {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    border: 1px solid #62543e;
    padding: 0.4rem;
    box-shadow: 2px 2px 4px #c2b79b;
    background-color: #f8f6f2;
  }

  .right {
    float: right;
    margin-left: 2rem;
  }

  .center {
    display: block;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
  }

  .intro-row {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    align-items: stretch;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .intro-row p {
    margin: 0;
    flex: 1;
  }

  .intro-video {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: auto;
    max-width: 200px;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  .final-media {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    clear: both;
  }

  .tilt-right-5 {
    transform: rotate(5deg);
  }

  .tilt-right-2 {
    transform: rotate(2deg);
  }

  .tilt-left-2 {
    transform: rotate(-2deg);
  }

  .footer {
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
  }
</style>
